com.snapbundle.model.context

Interface ITag

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IAccountContext, IDomainResource<ITag>, IMoniker, INamedObject<ITag>, IUrnNamespace
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Tag

    public interface ITag
extends INamedObject<ITag>, IAccountContext
    Defines a word or phrase useful for searching across related objects. Whereas the ITypedObject captures ontological categories similar to a table of contents, tags are used to capture data more commonly thought of as being found in the index of a book, not a table of contents.

    Tags are unique within a given account context.

    An Object might be assigned a type of "Bank Account" and certain Object Interactions related to the register of that bank account might be tagged as "High Value Transactions" if the dollar amount is over a certain threshold. This would permit a data analyst to query the system for all "High Value" transactions against "Bank Account" records, eliminating "High Value" transactions against "Retail Account" objects.
